.name
RayShade
.author
Craig E Kolb
Amiga Port by Martin Hohl 
.version
4.0
.description
Rayshade is a ray tracing program ported to the Amiga from UNIX.
Rayshade's features include eleven types of primitives (blob, box, cone,
cylinder, height field, plane, polygon, sphere, torus, flatand Phong-shaded
triangle); composite objects; point, directional, and extended (area) spot,
and quadrilateral light sources; solid procedural texturing and bump
mapping of primitives; antialiasing through variablerate "jittered"
sampling; arbitrary linear transformations on objects and texture/bump
maps; Use of uniform spatial subdivision or hierarchy of bounding volumes
to speed rendering; options to facilitate rendering of stereo pairs;
rudimentary animation support, and more.  Patchlevel 6, and includes
sources in C.  The modifications for Amiga & SAS/C are distributed as diff
files.  Some example input files are also included.  This is an update to
version 3.0 on disk 596.  
